node.text: Europe’s biggest free and open motorcycle event returned to the stunning Lake Faak earlier this month. Thousands of riders made the pilgrimage to Austria’s very own “Harleywood”, where the Sportster S and @HDPanAmerica took top billing, alongside the fantastic scenery, riding roads and hospitality that make this part of Europe so amazing to visit. Next year’s event will take place September 6-11, 2022. Come and join us!

node.text:
We’re proud to partner with @WWP on Operation Personal Freedom to raise funds and awareness for the mental health challenges that many servicemen and women face. Roughly one-third of our U.S. riders are veterans and together we can do more for those who have done so much for us. ​

Learn more at the link in our bio & donate online or at your local Harley-Davidson dealer through November 14.

node.text:
After learning to ride at Riding Academy, Cindy decided to become a Riding Academy Coach to help others pursue their dreams.​

Are you a passionate rider looking to improve your skills, increase your safety knowledge, and share the love of riding with others? Talk to your H-D dealer about becoming a Riding Academy coach. Learn more at the link in our bio.

node.text: Europe’s biggest free and open motorcycle event returned to the stunning Lake Faak earlier this month. Thousands of riders made the pilgrimage to Austria’s very own “Harleywood”, where the Sportster S and @HDPanAmerica took top billing, alongside the fantastic scenery, riding roads and hospitality that make this part of Europe so amazing to visit. Next year’s event will take place September 6-11, 2022. Come and join us!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harley-Davidson on September 17, 2021 tagging @hdmuseum. May be a black-and-white image of one or more people, motorcycle and outdoors.

node.text:
Mother-daughter duo Fay and Mrs. S. J. Hildabrand made the trek from their home in Pennsylvania to visit family in Oklahoma in 1915. En route, the Hildabrands visited the Milwaukee Motorcycle Club and the #HarleyDavidson factory, where they befriended H-D employees and fellow female riders Crystal Haydel and Lillian Hauerwas. The Milwaukeeans gathered a group of motorcyclists and rode with the Hildabrands toward their next destination, Lake Geneva. ​

Pictured in the first photo is Fay and Mrs. S. J. Hildabrand outside of the Juneau Ave factory in Milwaukee with William S. Harley. The second photo shows the group of Milwaukeeans including the Hildabrands as well as Crystal and Lillian. In the background of the third photo taken on their way to Lake Geneva is Crystal Haydel, who was one of the first female employees at Harley-Davidson. She started in 1907 and eventually became a member of the Board of Directors in 1919.

node.text:
Harley-Davidson commissioned one-of-a-kind Sportster S & Pan America helmet designs from Nuno Henriques, better known by @hellocousteau.​

Making a living designing a bit of everything, Nuno has carved out a diverse career in some of the world’s best design offices. After opening his own interior design office in Portugal in 2015, Nuno never thought the next step would be to design custom helmet graphics. Today, Nuno works with dozens of brands and private clients from around the world to create unique works of helmet art.

node.text: Born to outperform. The next chapter in a century of legendary V-Twins is here. Check out these highlights of H-D Screamin' Eagle factory team riders @KyleWyman & @twyman_10 taking the 2021 Sportster S out for a spin. Learn more at the link in our bio.​
